ttribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["A perennially popular given name, of Continental Germanic origin, from <i>haim</i> ‘home’ + <i>rīc</i> ‘power, ruler’. It was an Old French name, adopted by the Normans and introduced by them to Britain. It has been borne by eight kings of England. Not until the 17th century did the form <i>Henry</i> (as opposed to   Harry  ) become the standard vernacular form, mainly under the influence of the Latin form <i>Henricus</i> and French <i>Henri</i>."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Henry Greystroke was born as the son of Ralph F Greystroke and Alice De Audley. He had at least 1 daughter with Joan Fitzhugh."},"et":{"–":"Surnud","–Male":"Surnud","–Female":"Surnud","1352–1381":"1352–1381","1299–1323":"1299–1323","1300–1374":"1300–1374","1323":"1323","1300":"1300","1299":"1299","1352":"1352","1374":"1374","1381":"1381","Deighton, Yorkshire, England":"Deighton, Yorkshire, England"},"fi":{"–":"Kuollut","–Male":"Kuollut","–Female":"Kuollut","1352–1381":"1352–1381","1299–1323":"1299–1323","1300–1374":"1300–1374","1323":"1323","1300":"1300","1299":"1299","1352":"1352","1374":"1374","1381":"1381","Deighton, Yorkshire, England":"Deighton, Yorkshire, England"},"fr":{"–":"Décédé","–Male":"Décédé","–Female":"Décédée","1352–1381":"1352–1381","1299–1323":"1299–1323","1300–1374":"1300–1374","1323":"1323","1300":"1300","1299":"1299","1352":"1352","1374":"1374","1381":"1381","Deighton, Yorkshire, England":"Deighton, Everwyck, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Henry Greystroke est né, fils de Ralph F Greystroke et Alice De Audley. Il a eu au moins 1 fille avec Joan Fitzhugh."},"de":{"–":"Verstorben","–Male":"Verstorben","–Female":"Verstorben","1352–1381":"1352–1381","1299–1323":"1299–1323","1300–1374":"1300–1374","1323":"1323","1300":"1300","1299":"1299","1352":"1352","1374":"1374","1381":"1381","Deighton, Yorkshire, England":"Deighton, Yorkshire, England","lifeSummary":"Henry Greystroke wurd